Package com.rubynaxela.kyanite.math

package com.rubynaxela.kyanite.math
Contains classes representing geometric structures and providing mathematical calculations
  • Class
    Description
    Direction
    A simple enum for representing the four cardinal and four intercardinal directions on a two-dimensional plane.
    Direction.Axis
    The two axes of a 2D plane - X and Y.
    FloatLine
    Represents a line segment connecting two points using floating point coordinates.
    FloatRect
    Represents an axis-aligned rectangle using floating point coordinates.
    IntLine
    Represents a line segment connecting two points using floating point coordinates.
    IntRect
    Represents an axis-aligned rectangle using integer coordinates.
    MathUtils
    A set of mathematical constants, functions and algorithms.
    MathUtils.ElementaryTransform
    Elementary transformations of the identity matrix.
    Vec2
    Provides aliases for Vector2f's and Vector2i's constructors as well as arithmetic operations with both types.
    Vec3
    Provides aliases for Vector3f's and Vector3i's constructors as well as arithmetic operations with both types.
    Vector2f
    Represents two-dimensional vectors using floating point coordinates.
    Vector2i
    Represents two-dimensional vectors using integer coordinates.
    Vector3f
    Represents three-dimensional vectors using floating point coordinates.
    Vector3i
    Represents three-dimensional vectors using integer coordinates.
